{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BJRQ4fpDiBqWBTYhZuqc4P","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# ConversationHistory\n     2→\n     3→Renders a previously-completed conversation from the server, including message hydration and performance telemetry.\n     4→\n     5→## Component tree\n     6→\n     7→```text\n     8→ConversationHistory\n     9→ ├── useConversationPerfTracker(conversationId, traceResults, clientFetchStartTime, clientFetchEndTime)  // creates per-nav perf tracker\n    10→ ├── useHydrateMessages(conversationResponse, tracker)         // parse + hydrate Jotai atoms\n    11→ └── Chat                                                      // renders message list (lazy-loaded)\n    12→```\n    13→\n    14→## Instrumentation overview\n    15→\n    16→Performance instrumentation spans the full request lifecycle across server and client:\n    17→\n    18→| Layer | File | Mechanism | Purpose |\n    19→|-------|------|-----------|---------|\n    20→| Server | `apps/bebop/.../fetchConversation.ts` | `markEvent(perfTracker, ...)` | Point-in-time events logged by `requestLoggingMiddleware` |\n    21→| Server | `apps/bebop/.../fetchConversation.ts` | `SimpleTracer` spans | Span durations returned as `traceResults` for client-side devtools |\n    22→| Client | `useHydrateMessages.ts` | `tracker.markHydrationStart/End()` | Produces `hydrationMS` via tracker instance (replaces global `performance.mark`) |\n    23→| Client | `useConversationPerfTracker.ts` | double-rAF | Fires `ConversationHistoryLatency` telemetry event via `ConversationPerfTracker` |\n    24→| Client | `ConversationPerfTracker.ts` | Class with `#private` state | Encapsulates all timing data per navigation, finalized once |\n    25→| Client | `conversationPerfAtoms.ts` | Jotai atoms | Persists active tracker + history of finalized trackers across navigations |\n    26→| Client | `conversationsQueryOptions.ts` | `performance.now()` around `fetchConversation()` | Captures client-side round-trip timing (`clientFetchStartTime` / `clientFetchEndTime`) |\n    27→| Client | `ConversationHistory.tsx` (apps/bebop) | Passes `traceResults` and client fetch timing from server response | Enables fetch tracing when `enableDevTools` query param is set |\n    28→\n    29→### Server-side `markEvent` events\n    30→\n    31→The `fetchConversation` server function emits the following events via `markEvent(perfTracker, ...)`, which are auto-logged by `requestLoggingMiddleware`:\n    32→\n    33→| Event | When |\n    34→|-------|------|\n    35→| `handler_entered` | Function entry |\n    36→| `get_conversation_start` | Before `getConversation()` API call |\n    37→| `get_conversation_complete` | After `getConversation()` returns |\n    38→| `conversation_not_found` | Error/empty path (conversation is null) |\n    39→| `response_serialized` | End of success path, before returning to client |\n    40→\n    41→These events complement the `SimpleTracer` spans (which provide `serverFetchMS` and `server_*` breakdowns on the client) by giving server-side request-level observability without requiring client instrumentation.\n    42→\n    43→## ConversationPerfTracker\n    44→\n    45→Each conversation navigation creates a fresh `ConversationPerfTracker` instance that holds all timing data privately. This replaces the previous approach of using global `performance.mark()` calls and a render-less reporter component, ensuring telemetry isolation between navigations.\n    46→\n    47→### Lifecycle\n    48→\n    49→1. `useConversationPerfTracker` creates a new tracker via `useState` initializer (once per mount).\n    50→2. The tracker is stored in `activeConversationPerfTrackerAtom` for external access.\n    51→3. `useHydrateMessages` calls `tracker.markHydrationStart()` / `tracker.markHydrationEnd()` during render.\n    52→4. A `useLayoutEffect` captures `renderStartTime` and starts a double-rAF to detect first paint.\n    53→5. Once paint is detected, the tracker finalizes immediately — computing derived metrics, saving to PAS, and firing telemetry. No deferred timeout is needed because `traceResults` are resolved by `useSuspenseQuery` before the component mounts.\n    54→6. After finalization, the tracker is archived into `conversationPerfHistoryAtom`.\n    55→7. The component remounts on conversation switch (parent Suspense uses `key={conversationId}`), so a fresh tracker is created per navigation.\n    56→\n    57→### Jotai atoms\n    58→\n    59→| Atom | Purpose |\n    60→|------|---------|\n    61→| `activeConversationPerfTrackerAtom` | Current in-flight tracker (set on mount, replaced on next navigation) |\n    62→| `conversationPerfHistoryAtom` | Ordered list of finalized trackers from previous navigations |\n    63→| `archiveActiveTrackerAtom` | Write atom that moves the active tracker into history after finalization |\n    64→\n    65→## Telemetry: `ConversationHistoryLatency`\n    66→\n    67→Fired once per conversation load by `ConversationPerfTracker.finalize()`.\n    68→\n    69→### Timing flow\n    70→\n    71→```text\n    72→ Client fetch (network + server + transfer)     Hydrate atoms            Render + commit    First paint + finalize\n    73→─────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────┬──────────────────┬──────────────────┐\n    74→     │          clientFetchDurationMS            │      hydrationMS         │    paintMS       │                  │\n    75→     │◄────────────────────────────────────────►│◄────────────────────────►│◄───────────────►│                  │\n    76→     │     (includes serverFetchMS internally)   │                                                                │\n    77→     │                                           │◄──────────── clientRenderMS ──────────────────────────────────►│\n    78→     │                                           │  (hydrationStart → rafPaintTime)                                │\n    79→     │                                                                                                            │\n    80→     │◄──────────────────────────────── totalDurationMS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────►│\n    81→     │  (clientFetchDurationMS + clientRenderMS)                                                                   │\n    82→```\n    83→\n    84→`clientFetchDurationMS` is measured client-side via `performance.now()` around the `fetchConversation()` call. It captures the full round-trip: network + server processing + transfer. This is always available when the fetch runs in the query function.\n    85→`serverFetchMS` is the server-side processing duration from `TraceResults`. Kept as a supplementary breakdown metric. Used as fallback for `totalDurationMS` when client fetch timing is unavailable.\n    86→`clientRenderMS` spans from hydration start to first paint, covering all client-side work.\n    87→`paintMS` isolates the commit → paint time (after React commits DOM, before browser paints).\n    88→`totalDurationMS` is the full end-to-end duration: `clientFetchDurationMS + clientRenderMS` (falls back to `serverFetchMS + clientRenderMS` if client timing is unavailable).\n    89→\n    90→### Metrics\n    91→\n    92→| Metric | Type | Description |\n    93→|---|---|---|\n    94→| `conversationId` | `string` | ID of the loaded conversation |\n    95→| `messageCount` | `number` | Total messages (user + bot) in the conversation |\n    96→| `clientFetchDurationMS` | `number?` | Client-side round-trip duration measured via `performance.now()` around `fetchConversation()`. Captures network + server processing + transfer. Undefined if client fetch timing was not provided. |\n    97→| `serverFetchMS` | `number?` | Server-side processing duration from `TraceResults`. Supplementary breakdown metric. Used as fallback for `totalDurationMS` when client fetch timing is unavailable. |\n    98→| `hydrationMS` | `number?` | Time spent in `useHydrateMessages`: mapping the API response, parsing markdown to React elements, and hydrating Jotai atoms. Measured via tracker instance timestamps (no global marks). |\n    99→| `clientRenderMS` | `number` | Time from hydration start to first paint frame (double-rAF). Covers all client-side work: parsing, atom hydration, React render/commit, and browser paint. Falls back to layout-effect mount time if hydration marks are unavailable. |\n   100→| `paintMS` | `number?` | Time from React commit (layout effect) to first paint (double-rAF). Isolates the browser paint cost from hydration. |\n   101→| `totalDurationMS` | `number?` | Full end-to-end duration: `clientFetchDurationMS + clientRenderMS` (falls back to `serverFetchMS + clientRenderMS`). Undefined if neither fetch timing is available. |\n   102→| `loafTotalBlockingTime` | `number` | Sum of blocking time from Long Animation Frames (LoAF) during the hydration-to-paint span |\n   103→| `loafFrameCount` | `number` | Number of LoAF entries in the span |\n   104→| `loafMaxDuration` | `number` | Duration of the longest LoAF entry in the span |\n   105→| `server_*` | `number` | Per-span server breakdowns from `TraceResults.spans` (e.g. `server_get-auth-header`, `server_get-conversation-api-call`, `server_parse-response`) |\n   106→\n   107→### PAS (Page Action Signal) metrics\n   108→\n   109→The following are also written to page timings via `saveToPageTimings`:\n   110→\n   111→- `convHistory_clientFetchDurationMS`\n   112→- `convHistory_serverFetchMS`\n   113→- `convHistory_hydrationMS`\n   114→- `convHistory_clientRenderMS`\n   115→- `convHistory_paintMS`\n   116→- `convHistory_totalDurationMS`\n   117→- `convHistory_messageCount`\n   118→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XrfUS8UeV8YDsw48sFBkQR","session_id":"8a2fc4e6-c1a3-49e6-ae99-e4ee481c1eee","uuid":"59242119-0f3e-47eb-98c7-d73ccf397b3c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FYEFUkGR37RZxEwsuEsFmk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { useChatMode } from '../Chat/hooks/useChatMode';\n     2→import { ChatInput } from '../../../input/components/ChatInput/ChatInput';\n     3→import { ChatInputToggle } from '../../../input/components/ChatInput/ChatInputToggle';\n     4→import type { SubmitPromptParameters } from '@bebopjs/bebop-ux';\n     5→import type { Status } from '@bebopjs/bebop-response-mapping';\n     6→import type { FC, RefObject } from 'react';\n     7→\n     8→export interface ChatPromptProps {\n     9→  startSpan: () => void;\n    10→  endSpan: () => void;\n    11→  responseStatus: Status | null;\n    12→  setResponseStatus: (status: Status | null) => void;\n    13→  submitPrompt: (parameters: SubmitPromptParameters) => void;\n    14→  abortControllerRef: RefObject<AbortController | null>;\n    15→  conversationId?: string;\n    16→  initialPrompt?: string;\n    17→}\n    18→\n    19→export const ChatPrompt: FC<ChatPromptProps> = (props) => {\n    20→  const {\n    21→    startSpan,\n    22→    responseStatus,\n    23→    setResponseStatus,\n    24→    submitPrompt,\n    25→    abortControllerRef,\n    26→    conversationId,\n    27→    initialPrompt\n    28→  } = props;\n    29→  const { mode, actions } = useChatMode();\n    30→  const { collapsed } = mode;\n    31→  const { expand, fill, empty, pin, collapse } = actions;\n    32→\n    33→  if (collapsed) {\n    34→    return <ChatInputToggle expand={expand} collapse={collapse} />;\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  return (\n    38→    <ChatInput\n    39→      onInteractionStart={startSpan}\n    40→      onSubmitPromptStart={pin}\n    41→      onUpdateInput={fill}\n    42→      onClearInput={empty}\n    43→      submitPrompt={submitPrompt}\n    44→      responseStatus={responseStatus}\n    45→      setResponseStatus={setResponseStatus}\n    46→      abortControllerRef={abortControllerRef}\n    47→      conversationId={conversationId}\n    48→      initialPrompt={initialPrompt}\n    49→    />\n    50→  );\n    51→};\n    52→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XrfUS8UeV8YDsw48sFBkQR","session_id":"8a2fc4e6-c1a3-49e6-ae99-e4ee481c1eee","uuid":"80f7e791-2fee-460f-9ffa-903f8a1fc6c9"}
