{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XrfUS8UeV8YDsw48sFBkQR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create the final report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Bebop App Exploration Report\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Bebop app. Here are the findings:\n\n### 1. CLAUDE.md & Documentation Files\n\n**Root CLAUDE.md:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/CLAUDE.md` (lines 1-161)\n- Comprehensive repo overview for office-bohemia monorepo (~200 packages)\n- Core architectural concepts: Loop Components, Fluid Framework containers, WorkspaceComponent\n- Testing, deployment, code style guidelines for the entire repo\n\n**Bebop CLAUDE.md:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/CLAUDE.md` (lines 1-5)\n- References AGENTS.md and CONTRIBUTING.md\n\n**Bebop AGENTS.md & CONTRIBUTING.md:** Referenced at `apps/bebop/AGENTS.md` and `apps/bebop/CONTRIBUTING.md`\n- TanStack Start React application with SSR, React Server Components, React Compiler\n- Feature-first organization: `src/features/<feature>/` with subfolders for components, atoms, hooks, queries, mutations, serverFunctions, server, client\n- State split: TanStack Query for remote state, Jotai for local UI state\n- Dependency flow: routes → features → core/shared (never core → features)\n\n**Bebop README.md:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/README.md` (lines 1-200)\n- Development setup, HMR at `https://m365.cloud.dev.microsoft:3001`\n- Bundle analysis, environment configuration, deployment pipelines to CDN\n\n### 2. Route Structure\n\n**All route files in `apps/bebop/src/routes/`:**\n\n| Route File | Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|---------|\n| `__root.tsx` | Root route | App initialization, layout |\n| `_mainLayout.tsx` (lines 1-52) | Layout route | Main app layout, Nav, dialogs, telemetry lazy-loading |\n| `_mainLayout.index.tsx` (lines 1-39) | `/` | New chat page with RealtimeVoiceProvider, resets messages |\n| `_mainLayout.conversation.$conversationId.tsx` (lines 1-75) | `/conversation/{id}` | View existing conversation with ConversationHistory |\n| `_mainLayout.conversations/index.tsx` | `/conversations/` | Alternative conversation view with ConversationView |\n| `_mainLayout.agents.tsx` | `/agents` | Agents route |\n| `_mainLayout.blank.tsx` | `/blank` | Blank page route |\n| `_mainLayout.search.tsx` | `/search` | Search conversations |\n| `_mainLayout.workspace.$workspaceId.tsx` | `/workspace/{id}` | Workspace navigation |\n| `_mainLayout.workspaces.tsx` | `/workspaces` | List workspaces |\n| `adaptive.tsx` | `/adaptive` | Adaptive mode test |\n| Demo/Test routes | `/demos/*`, `/measure/*` | Development testing routes |\n\n**Key Observation:** NO `/cowork` or cowork-related routes found (despite PR history mention of `_mainLayout.cowork.tsx`)\n\n### 3. Features Structure\n\n**Features directory:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/`\n\n| Feature | Subfolders/Purpose |\n|---------|-------------------|\n| **conversation** | Core chat experience - ConversationHistory, Chat component, chat mode atoms, server functions for Sydney integration |\n| **conversations** | Conversation management - list, detail, rename, delete, search functionality |\n| **input** | User input - ChatInput (Lexical-based editor), Voice interaction, ChatInputTools |\n| **nav** | Navigation - Nav component, user profile queries |\n| **devTools** | Development utilities |\n| **intentDetection** | Intent detection for query routing |\n\n### 4. Backend Communication Patterns\n\n**Server Functions (TanStack Start `createServerFn`):**\n\n1. **Chat Request:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/chat.ts` (lines 1-103)\n   - Endpoint: POST to `requestChat`\n   - Input: `{ clientRequestId, message, traceId, conversationId, queryAnnotations, sydneyReplayFixture?, sydneyRecordMode? }`\n   - Returns: `ReadableStream<string>` for streaming responses\n   - Handles replay fixtures (dev/test) and live Sydney mode\n\n2. **Streaming Pipeline:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/utils/getSydneyStream.ts` (lines 1-354)\n   - Creates `ReadableStream` from Sydney backend\n   - Markdown parsing via `makeMarkdownToHtmlParser`\n   - Response mapping via `createSydneyResponseMapper`\n   - Supports `writeAtCursor` incremental markdown updates\n   - WebSocket integration with Sydney client\n   - Performance tracing with spans: `waiting_for_sydney`, `searching_and_reasoning`, `parser_buffering_markdown`, `streaming_chunks`\n\n3. **Streaming Emission:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/utils/emitResultToStream.ts` (lines 1-45)\n   - `emitResultToStream()`: HTML + mutations to controller\n   - `emitConversationState()`: JSON script tag with conversation ID\n   - `emitServerMetrics()`: Performance metrics\n   - `emitTraceResults()`: Trace results for devtools\n\n4. **Query Options:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/queryOptions/requestChatQuery.ts` (lines 1-59)\n   - Uses TanStack Query `experimental_streamedQuery`\n   - Creates async iterable from `requestChat`\n   - Immediate stale, zero gcTime, no retry\n\n5. **Conversation Fetching:**\n   - `fetchConversation.ts` (lines 1-92): Loads conversation history with Sydney auth\n   - Uses `getConversation()` from `@bebopjs/bebop-services`\n   - Returns `ConversationResponse` with `traceResults`\n\n6. **Conversations List:**\n   - `fetchConversations.ts`: Infinite query for conversation list\n   - `fetchConversations` with pageParam for pagination\n\n**WebSocket/Network:**\n- No explicit WebSocket code in bebop app\n- Sydney client (`@bebopjs/bebop-sydney-client`) handles WebSocket connection\n- Constructor utility: `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/utils/getWebSocketConstructor.ts`\n\n### 5. Cowork Route Implementation\n\n**Status:** NO existing cowork implementation in the current codebase.\n\n**Evidence:**\n- No files matching `*cowork*` pattern\n- grep for \"cowork\" returns zero results in routes\n- PR history mentions `_mainLayout.cowork.tsx` but it doesn't exist\n\n### 6. AugLoop Integration\n\n**Findings:** NO AugLoop/Fluid Framework integration in Bebop app itself.\n\n- Grep for \"augloop\", \"AugLoop\", \"aug-loop\", \"fluid\" returns only container references in shared types\n- Bebop is the **frontend** consuming APIs (Sydney backend, Conversation API)\n- Real-time collaboration is handled via `RealtimeVoiceProvider` from `@bebopjs/bebop-ux` (external package)\n\n### 7. 1JS Framework Integration\n\n**Found in:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversations/serverFunctions/fetchConversation.ts` (line 74)\n\n```typescript\n// Line 74: \"However, the TypeScript return type `ConversationResponse` includes types from @1js/sydney-types\"\n```\n\n**Context:**\n- `ConversationResponse` type comes from `@bebopjs/bebop-shared-types`\n- Imports session types from `@1js/sydney-types` (1JS = Office.js framework)\n- Types include `IAdaptiveCard`, `SessionMessage` with function signatures that don't serialize\n- Workaround: Type assertion to `any` for TanStack Start serialization\n\n**No direct 1JS integration in Bebop** - Bebop consumes types only, not the framework itself.\n\n### 8. Chat Feature Deep Dive\n\n**Chat Components Tree:**\n\n```\nConversationHistory / _mainLayout.index route\n├── RealtimeVoiceProvider\n├── useHydrateMessages() - Hydrates Jotai atoms from server response\n├── useConversationPerfTracker() - Performance tracking\n└── Chat component\n    ├── JotaiTranscript\n    │   ├── StreamingProvider\n    │   ├── PortalBridge\n    │   └── messages.map(messageId) → LazyChatResponse (Suspense)\n    └── JotaiChatPromptWrapper\n        ├── useChatOrchestration hook\n        ├── useLoAFSpan() - Performance span\n        └── ChatPrompt\n            ├── ChatInputToggle (if collapsed)\n            └── ChatInput (Lexical editor)\n```\n\n**Message Rendering:**\n- `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/components/Chat/JotaiTranscript.tsx` (lines 1-39)\n  - Uses `messageOrderAtom` from `@bebopjs/bebop-ux`\n  - Lazy-loads `LazyChatResponse` component per message\n  - Wraps in `StreamingProvider` and `PortalBridge`\n\n**Streaming Progression:**\n1. Server: `getSydneyStream()` creates ReadableStream\n2. Client: `requestChatQueryOptions()` converts stream to async iterable\n3. Parser: Markdown → HTML with mutation tracking\n4. Emit: Enqueues HTML + mutations to client\n5. Hydration: `useHydrateMessages()` updates atoms\n6. Render: `messageOrderAtom` drives `JotaiTranscript` list\n\n### 9. RealtimeVoiceProvider & Chat Integration\n\n**Located in:** `@bebopjs/bebop-ux` (external package)\n\n**Bebop usage:**\n- `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/components/ConversationHistory/ConversationHistory.tsx` (lines 1-27)\n  - Wraps `Chat` component\n  - Calls `useHydrateMessages()` and `useConversationPerfTracker()`\n  \n- `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/routes/_mainLayout.index.tsx` (lines 1-39)\n  - Wraps root Chat in `RealtimeVoiceProvider`\n  - Resets messages on route change via `resetMessagesAtom`\n\n**Voice Input:**\n- `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/input/components/Voice/VoiceOverlayDisplay.tsx`\n- Integrated via `VoiceButton` in ChatInput (line 378)\n- Lazy-loaded on hover via `Prefetch` component\n\n### 10. Jotai Atoms State Management\n\n**Chat-related atoms:**\n\n| Atom File | Atoms | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------|---------|\n| `atoms/chatModeAtoms.ts` (lines 1-50) | `chatModeAtom`, `chatModeDispatchAtom` | Chat UI mode state: pinned, collapsed, filled |\n| `components/Chat/hooks/useChatMode.ts` (lines 1-47) | - | Hook providing mode + actions (pin, collapse, expand, fill, empty) |\n| `components/Chat/hooks/useChatScrollMode.ts` (lines 1-123) | - | Scroll detection dispatches chat mode actions (pin on scroll down, expand on scroll up) |\n\n**Conversation atoms:**\n\n| Atom File | Atoms | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------|---------|\n| `features/conversations/atoms/conversationAtoms.ts` (lines 1-13) | `conversationUnderEditAtom`, `isConversationEditingAtom` | Track which conversation is being renamed |\n| `features/conversations/atoms/conversationsSearchAtoms.ts` (lines 1-11) | `isSearchModeAtom`, `conversationsSearchQueryAtom`, `exitSearchAtom` | Search state management |\n| `features/conversations/atoms/dialogAtoms.ts` (lines 1-17) | `activeDialogAtom` | Active dialog (DeleteConversation) state |\n\n**Input atoms:**\n\n| Atom File | Atoms | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------|---------|\n| `features/input/atoms/voiceInteractionAtoms.ts` (lines 1-8) | `showVoiceOverlayAtom` | Voice overlay visibility |\n\n**Nav atoms:**\n\n| Atom File | Atoms | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------|---------|\n| `features/nav/atoms/navAtoms.ts` (lines 1-9) | `isNavExpandedAtom` | Nav expanded/collapsed state |\n\n**External atoms (from bebop-ux package):**\n- `hasMessagesAtom` - Determines if chat has messages\n- `messageOrderAtom` - Ordered list of message IDs for rendering\n- `conversationIdAtom` - Current conversation ID\n- `resetMessagesAtom` - Write atom to reset all messages\n- `selectedTextAtom` - Selected text in editor\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Bebop Architecture:**\n- TanStack Start RSC app with streaming SSR\n- Feature-based organization (conversation, conversations, input, nav, intentDetection)\n- Sydney backend integration for AI chat via ReadableStream streaming\n- Markdown parsing → HTML rendering with incremental updates\n- Jotai for local UI state, TanStack Query for remote state\n- Performance instrumentation end-to-end (server marks → client traces)\n- RealtimeVoiceProvider for voice I/O (external)\n- No cowork/collaboration features in current codebase\n- 1JS types referenced but no direct framework integration\n\n**Key Files for Development:**\n- Routes: `apps/bebop/src/routes/` (thin, orchestrate only)\n- Features: `apps/bebop/src/features/{conversation,conversations,input,nav}/`\n- Chat streaming: `features/conversation/serverFunctions/utils/getSydneyStream.ts`\n- Atoms: Multiple feature-specific Jotai atom definitions\n- Components: Chat, ChatInput (Lexical), ConversationHistory"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6e82d0798b71b5fd (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 93866\ntool_uses: 63\nduration_ms: 219980</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a2fc4e6-c1a3-49e6-ae99-e4ee481c1eee","uuid":"b166703c-b8ea-4d89-9bd8-16ad33881fe1","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the Bebop app in the office-bohemia repo at C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read CLAUDE.md at root if it exists\n2. Read apps/bebop/CLAUDE.md or apps/bebop/README.md if they exist\n3. Map the route structure under apps/bebop/src/routes/ — list all route files\n4. Explore apps/bebop/src/features/ — what features exist? Focus on chat, cowork, collaboration features\n5. Find how Bebop communicates with backend agents — search for API calls, fetch, WebSocket, SSE in the bebop app\n6. Look for any existing cowork route implementation (we know _mainLayout.cowork.tsx exists from PR history)\n7. Find AugLoop integration — search for \"augloop\", \"AugLoop\", \"aug-loop\", \"fluid\" references in the bebop app\n8. Look for 1JS framework integration patterns — search for \"1js\", \"oneJS\", \"one-js\", \"OfficeJS\", \"office-js\"\n9. Examine the chat feature deeply — how does it render messages, handle streaming, show progression?\n10. Look at how the RealtimeVoiceProvider and Chat component work\n11. Find Jotai atoms related to chat/messages — what state management exists?\n\nBe very thorough. Report file paths with line numbers for everything you find.","agentId":"a6e82d0798b71b5fd","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create the final report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Bebop App Exploration Report\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Bebop app. Here are the findings:\n\n### 1. CLAUDE.md & Documentation Files\n\n**Root CLAUDE.md:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/CLAUDE.md` (lines 1-161)\n- Comprehensive repo overview for office-bohemia monorepo (~200 packages)\n- Core architectural concepts: Loop Components, Fluid Framework containers, WorkspaceComponent\n- Testing, deployment, code style guidelines for the entire repo\n\n**Bebop CLAUDE.md:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/CLAUDE.md` (lines 1-5)\n- References AGENTS.md and CONTRIBUTING.md\n\n**Bebop AGENTS.md & CONTRIBUTING.md:** Referenced at `apps/bebop/AGENTS.md` and `apps/bebop/CONTRIBUTING.md`\n- TanStack Start React application with SSR, React Server Components, React Compiler\n- Feature-first organization: `src/features/<feature>/` with subfolders for components, atoms, hooks, queries, mutations, serverFunctions, server, client\n- State split: TanStack Query for remote state, Jotai for local UI state\n- Dependency flow: routes → features → core/shared (never core → features)\n\n**Bebop README.md:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/README.md` (lines 1-200)\n- Development setup, HMR at `https://m365.cloud.dev.microsoft:3001`\n- Bundle analysis, environment configuration, deployment pipelines to CDN\n\n### 2. Route Structure\n\n**All route files in `apps/bebop/src/routes/`:**\n\n| Route File | Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|---------|\n| `__root.tsx` | Root route | App initialization, layout |\n| `_mainLayout.tsx` (lines 1-52) | Layout route | Main app layout, Nav, dialogs, telemetry lazy-loading |\n| `_mainLayout.index.tsx` (lines 1-39) | `/` | New chat page with RealtimeVoiceProvider, resets messages |\n| `_mainLayout.conversation.$conversationId.tsx` (lines 1-75) | `/conversation/{id}` | View existing conversation with ConversationHistory |\n| `_mainLayout.conversations/index.tsx` | `/conversations/` | Alternative conversation view with ConversationView |\n| `_mainLayout.agents.tsx` | `/agents` | Agents route |\n| `_mainLayout.blank.tsx` | `/blank` | Blank page route |\n| `_mainLayout.search.tsx` | `/search` | Search conversations |\n| `_mainLayout.workspace.$workspaceId.tsx` | `/workspace/{id}` | Workspace navigation |\n| `_mainLayout.workspaces.tsx` | `/workspaces` | List workspaces |\n| `adaptive.tsx` | `/adaptive` | Adaptive mode test |\n| Demo/Test routes | `/demos/*`, `/measure/*` | Development testing routes |\n\n**Key Observation:** NO `/cowork` or cowork-related routes found (despite PR history mention of `_mainLayout.cowork.tsx`)\n\n### 3. Features Structure\n\n**Features directory:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/`\n\n| Feature | Subfolders/Purpose |\n|---------|-------------------|\n| **conversation** | Core chat experience - ConversationHistory, Chat component, chat mode atoms, server functions for Sydney integration |\n| **conversations** | Conversation management - list, detail, rename, delete, search functionality |\n| **input** | User input - ChatInput (Lexical-based editor), Voice interaction, ChatInputTools |\n| **nav** | Navigation - Nav component, user profile queries |\n| **devTools** | Development utilities |\n| **intentDetection** | Intent detection for query routing |\n\n### 4. Backend Communication Patterns\n\n**Server Functions (TanStack Start `createServerFn`):**\n\n1. **Chat Request:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/chat.ts` (lines 1-103)\n   - Endpoint: POST to `requestChat`\n   - Input: `{ clientRequestId, message, traceId, conversationId, queryAnnotations, sydneyReplayFixture?, sydneyRecordMode? }`\n   - Returns: `ReadableStream<string>` for streaming responses\n   - Handles replay fixtures (dev/test) and live Sydney mode\n\n2. **Streaming Pipeline:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/utils/getSydneyStream.ts` (lines 1-354)\n   - Creates `ReadableStream` from Sydney backend\n   - Markdown parsing via `makeMarkdownToHtmlParser`\n   - Response mapping via `createSydneyResponseMapper`\n   - Supports `writeAtCursor` incremental markdown updates\n   - WebSocket integration with Sydney client\n   - Performance tracing with spans: `waiting_for_sydney`, `searching_and_reasoning`, `parser_buffering_markdown`, `streaming_chunks`\n\n3. **Streaming Emission:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/utils/emitResultToStream.ts` (lines 1-45)\n   - `emitResultToStream()`: HTML + mutations to controller\n   - `emitConversationState()`: JSON script tag with conversation ID\n   - `emitServerMetrics()`: Performance metrics\n   - `emitTraceResults()`: Trace results for devtools\n\n4. **Query Options:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/queryOptions/requestChatQuery.ts` (lines 1-59)\n   - Uses TanStack Query `experimental_streamedQuery`\n   - Creates async iterable from `requestChat`\n   - Immediate stale, zero gcTime, no retry\n\n5. **Conversation Fetching:**\n   - `fetchConversation.ts` (lines 1-92): Loads conversation history with Sydney auth\n   - Uses `getConversation()` from `@bebopjs/bebop-services`\n   - Returns `ConversationResponse` with `traceResults`\n\n6. **Conversations List:**\n   - `fetchConversations.ts`: Infinite query for conversation list\n   - `fetchConversations` with pageParam for pagination\n\n**WebSocket/Network:**\n- No explicit WebSocket code in bebop app\n- Sydney client (`@bebopjs/bebop-sydney-client`) handles WebSocket connection\n- Constructor utility: `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/serverFunctions/utils/getWebSocketConstructor.ts`\n\n### 5. Cowork Route Implementation\n\n**Status:** NO existing cowork implementation in the current codebase.\n\n**Evidence:**\n- No files matching `*cowork*` pattern\n- grep for \"cowork\" returns zero results in routes\n- PR history mentions `_mainLayout.cowork.tsx` but it doesn't exist\n\n### 6. AugLoop Integration\n\n**Findings:** NO AugLoop/Fluid Framework integration in Bebop app itself.\n\n- Grep for \"augloop\", \"AugLoop\", \"aug-loop\", \"fluid\" returns only container references in shared types\n- Bebop is the **frontend** consuming APIs (Sydney backend, Conversation API)\n- Real-time collaboration is handled via `RealtimeVoiceProvider` from `@bebopjs/bebop-ux` (external package)\n\n### 7. 1JS Framework Integration\n\n**Found in:** `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/src/features/conversations/serverFunctions/fetchConversation.ts` (line 74)\n\n```typescript\n// Line 74: \"However, the TypeScript return type `ConversationResponse` includes types from @1js/sydney-types\"\n```\n\n**Context:**\n- `ConversationResponse` type comes from `@bebopjs/bebop-shared-types`\n- Imports session types from `@1js/sydney-types` (1JS = Office.js framework)\n- Types include `IAdaptiveCard`, `SessionMessage` with function signatures that don't serialize\n- Workaround: Type assertion to `any` for TanStack Start serialization\n\n**No direct 1JS integration in Bebop** - Bebop consumes types only, not the framework itself.\n\n### 8. Chat Feature Deep Dive\n\n**Chat Components Tree:**\n\n```\nConversationHistory / _mainLayout.index route\n├── RealtimeVoiceProvider\n├── useHydrateMessages() - Hydrates Jotai atoms from server response\n├── useConversationPerfTracker() - Performance tracking\n└── Chat component\n    ├── JotaiTranscript\n    │   ├── StreamingProvider\n    │   ├── PortalBridge\n    │   └── messages.map(messageId) → LazyChatResponse (Suspense)\n    └── JotaiChatPromptWrapper\n        ├── useChatOrchestration hook\n        ├── useLoAFSpan() - Performance s