rates with AugLoop workflows\n  - Connection chain: OfficeAgentAsyncWorkflowLambda → OfficeAgentHandler → DocumentGenerationService → OfficePyClient → OfficePy Docker Container\n  - AugLoop acts as an orchestrator/proxy for auth, licensing, and callback services\n\n#### 2. **AugLoop Test Client**\n- **Main Client**: `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/augloop-client.ts` (382 lines)\n  - Implements `AugLoopClient` class\n  - Supports multiple environments: Dev, Local, Test, Int, Dogfood, MSIT, Prod, UsGov, Gallatin\n  - Key endpoints defined for each environment\n  - Functions:\n    - `getAugLoopAuthToken()` - authentication\n    - `sendAugLoopHttpRequest()` - HTTP POST to workflows\n    - `sendAugLoopWsRequest()` - WebSocket communication with annotation callbacks\n    - `disposeAugLoopSession()` - cleanup\n\n#### 3. **AugLoop Token Server Integration**\nMultiple schema files in `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/token-server/api/schemas/`:\n- `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/token-server/api/schemas/augloopPftPayload.ts`\n- `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/token-server/api/schemas/augloopPftPayloadGetTokenRequest.ts`\n- `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/token-server/api/schemas/augloopPftPayloadGetTokenRequestFlowType.ts`\n- `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/token-server/api/schemas/augloopClientTokenRequestPayload.ts`\n- `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/token-server/api/schemas/augloopClientTokenRequestPayloadGetTokenRequest.ts`\n- `/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/token-server/api/schemas/augloopClientTokenRequestPayloadGetTokenRequestFlowType.ts`\n\n#### 4. **AugLoop References** (181 total files)\nSpread across:\n- Settings files\n- WebSocket handlers\n- Message protocol definitions\n- Test utilities\n- Docker configuration\n\n#### 5. **1JS References** (43 total files)\n- No direct @1js framework patterns in OfficeAgent core\n- References appear in dependent packages and build configuration\n- Office.js integration in Excel/PowerPoint modules\n\n---\n\n### **COLLABORATIVE EDITING INFRASTRUCTURE**\n\n#### Fluid Framework Components\n- Base container infrastructure: `/office-bohemia/packages/base-container/`\n- Data models using Fluid primitives\n- Container definitions from @fluidframework packages\n\n#### AugLoop as Collaboration Hub\n- **Signal-based communication**: Signal operations for data synchronization\n- **Annotation system**: Type-based annotation activation and callbacks\n- **Session protocol**: WebSocket-based session management\n- **Delta resolution**: DeltaResolver for operational transforms\n\n---\n\n### **SUMMARY**\n\n**AugLoop** is a comprehensive collaboration framework used in office-bohemia as the primary augmentation and real-time collaboration engine. It integrates with **Fluid Framework** for distributed data structures and uses **Signal operations** and **Annotation callbacks** for collaborative features. \n\n**1JS (OneJS)** framework is used as a dependency in specific packages (calipso, m365-blaze-loader, scc-types, markdown-utils) with patches applied for m365-chat-context compatibility.\n\n**OfficeAgent** connects to AugLoop through a well-defined orchestration layer that manages authentication, WebSocket sessions, and workflow callbacks."}],"totalDurationMs":282945,"totalTokens":70511,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1453,"cache_read_input_tokens":66485,"output_tokens":2569,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1453},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
