{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W7ir1qdHDQkkW17a9ZSGfg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# AgentRequestMessage WebSocket Handling - End-to-End Flow\n     2→\n     3→This document explains how `AgentRequestMessage` is handled by created agents when received over WebSocket, from the initial connection through to Claude agent execution and response delivery.\n     4→\n     5→## Table of Contents\n     6→- [Overview](#overview)ture)\n     7→- [End-to-End Flow](#end-to-end-flow)\n     8→- [Detailed Component Breakdown](#detailed-component-breakdown)\n     9→- [Key Features](#key-features)\n    10→- [Error Handling](#error-handling)\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→The WebSocket-based agent request flow enables real-time, bidirectional communication between clients and Office Agent. When a client sends an `AgentRequestMessage` over WebSocket, it triggers a sophisticated pipeline involving message routing, preprocessing, validation, and ultimately Claude-based document generation.\n    17→\n    18→**Key Components:**\n    19→- **WebSocket Router** - Routes incoming messages to appropriate handlers\n    20→- **WebSocket Chat Request Handler** - Preprocesses and validates requests\n    21→- **Create Agent** - Main agent orchestrating document generation\n    22→- **Claude Agent SDK** - Executes document generation logic\n    23→\n    24→\n    25→---\n    26→\n    27→## End-to-End Flow\n    28→\n    29→```\n    30→┌──────────────┐\n    31→│   Client     │\n    32→└──────┬───────┘\n    33→       │ 1. Send AgentRequestMessage\n    34→       │    over WebSocket\n    35→       ▼\n    36→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    37→│  WebSocket Server                           │\n    38→│  (modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts)    │\n    39→│                                             │\n    40→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n    41→│  │  WebSocketRouter.routeMessage()      │  │\n    42→│  │  - Parse JSON message                │  │\n    43→│  │  - Extract message.type              │  │\n    44→│  │  - Find registered handler           │  │\n    45→│  └──────────┬───────────────────────────┘  │\n    46→└─────────────┼───────────────────────────────┘\n    47→              │ 2. Route to handler\n    48→              ▼\n    49→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    50→│  CreateAgent.handleChatRequest()            │\n    51→│  (agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts)  │\n    52→│                                             │\n    53→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n    54→│  │  PHASE 1: Preprocessing               │  │\n    55→│  │  ──────────────────────────────────   │  │\n    56→│  │  WebSocketChatRequestHandler          │  │\n    57→│  │  .preprocess(message)                 │  │\n    58→│  │  - Wait for session init              │  │\n    59→│  │  - Extract conversationId/requestId   │  │\n    60→│  │  - Check conversation busy state      │  │\n    61→│  │  - Validate query not empty           │  │\n    62→│  │  - Store query annotations            │  │\n    63→│  └──────────┬───────────────────────────┘  │\n    64→│             │ 3. Preprocessing result       │\n    65→│             ▼                               │\n    66→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n    67→│  │  PHASE 2: Send Acknowledgment         │  │\n    68→│  │  ──────────────────────────────────   │  │\n    69→│  │  Send ChatResponseMessage:            │  │\n    70→│  │  {                                    │  │\n    71→│  │    type: ChatResponse,                │  │\n    72→│  │    success: true/false,               │  │\n    73→│  │    requestId: \"...\",                  │  │\n    74→│  │    conversationId: \"...\",             │  │\n    75→│  │    error?: \"...\",                     │  │\n    76→│  │    errorMessage?: \"...\"               │  │\n    77→│  │  }                                    │  │\n    78→│  └──────────┬───────────────────────────┘  │\n    79→└─────────────┼───────────────────────────────┘\n    80→              │ 4. Continue if success\n    81→              ▼\n    82→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    83→│  PHASE 3: Parse Grounding Content           │\n    84→│  (grounding-content-parser.ts)              │\n    85→│  - Extract clarification questions          │\n    86→│  - Parse message annotations                │\n    87→│  - Append to user query if present          │\n    88→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n    89→           │ 5. Enhanced query\n    90→           ▼\n    91→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    92→│  PHASE 4: Initialize Services               │\n    93→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n    94→│  - FileWatcherService (monitor output)      │\n    95→│  - ClaudeMessageLoggerService               │\n    96→│  - WebSocketMessengerService                │\n    97→│  - DebugZipCreatorService                   │\n    98→│  - Performance tracking                     │\n    99→│  - Chain of thought tracking                │\n   100→│  - Query classifier                         │\n   101→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   102→           │ 6. Services ready\n   103→           ▼\n   104→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   105→│  PHASE 5: Create Turn & Execute Hooks       │\n   106→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   107→│  - workspaceManager.createNewTurn()         │\n   108→│  - Execute base startTurn hooks             │\n   109→│  - Execute agent-specific startTurn hooks   │\n   110→│  - Store grounding sources metadata         │\n   111→│  - Store query annotations metadata         │\n   112→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   113→           │ 7. Workspace ready\n   114→           ▼\n   115→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   116→│  PHASE 6: Build System Prompt               │\n   117→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   118→│  - Load agent capabilities                  │\n   119→│  - Load RAI guidelines                      │\n   120→│  - Load skill documentation (XLSX/DOCX/PPTX)│\n   121→│  - Build timestamp metadata                 │\n   122→│  - Render EJS template                      │\n   123→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   124→           │ 8. System prompt ready\n   125→           ▼\n   126→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   127→│  PHASE 7: Execute Claude Query              │\n   128→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   129→│  claude.query({                             │\n   130→│    prompt: userQuery + metadata,            │\n   131→│    options: {                               │\n   132→│      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-5',            │\n   133→│      maxTurns: 2000,                        │\n   134→│      systemPrompt: systemPrompt,            │\n   135→│      hooks: combinedHooks,                  │\n   136→│      env: { WORKSPACE_DIR, ... }            │\n   137→│    }                                        │\n   138→│  })                                         │\n   139→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   140→           │ 9. Stream Claude messages\n   141→           ▼\n   142→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   143→│  PHASE 8: Process Claude Messages           │\n   144→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   145→│  for await (message of queryIterator) {     │\n   146→│    - Log message to disk                    │\n   147→│    - Track performance metrics              │\n   148→│    - Track chain of thought                 │\n   149→│                                             │\n   150→│    if (message.type === 'result') {         │\n   151→│      - Summarize result message             │\n   152→│      - Send via ChatMessage/JSON-RPC        │\n   153→│      - Mark as complete                     │\n   154→│    }                                        │\n   155→│                                             │\n   156→│    if (interruptRequested) {                │\n   157→│      - Stop iteration                       │\n   158→│      - Send QueryInterrupted                │\n   159→│    }                                        │\n   160→│  }                                          │\n   161→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   162→           │ 10. Generation complete\n   163→           ▼\n   164→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   165→│  PHASE 9: Send Document Notifications       │\n   166→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   167→│  - Find generated files in output dir       │\n   168→│  - Determine primary document (.docx/.xlsx/ │\n   169→│    .pptx)                                   │\n   170→│                                             │\n   171→│  if (jsonRpcEnabled && isOfficeDocument) {  │\n   172→│    sendArtifactGenerationNotification()     │\n   173→│  } else {                                   │\n   174→│    sendDocumentGenerated()                  │\n   175→│  }                                          │\n   176→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   177→           │ 11. Document sent\n   178→           ▼\n   179→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   180→│  PHASE 10: Cleanup (finally block)          │\n   181→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   182→│  - Stop file watcher                        │\n   183→│  - Close chain of thought tracking          │\n   184→│  - Close Claude logger                      │\n   185→│  - Flush performance logs                   │\n   186→│  - Send fallback chat message if needed     │\n   187→│  - Create debug zip                         │\n   188→│  - Send task completion notification        │\n   189→│  - Mark conversation complete               │\n   190→│  - Clear interrupt flag                     │\n   191→│  - Fire-and-forget query classification     │\n   192→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   193→           │ 12. Cleanup complete\n   194→           ▼\n   195→┌──────────────┐\n   196→│   Client     │\n   197→│  (receives)  │\n   198→│  - ChatResponse (ack)                       │\n   199→│  - QueryStatus (file created events)        │\n   200→│  - DocumentGenerated                        │\n   201→│  - TaskCompletion                           │\n   202→└──────────────┘\n   203→```\n   204→\n   205→---\n   206→\n   207→## Detailed Component Breakdown\n   208→\n   209→### 1. WebSocket Router ([router.ts](../modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts))\n   210→\n   211→**Responsibility:** Routes incoming WebSocket messages to registered handlers.\n   212→\n   213→**Key Methods:**\n   214→- `registerHandler(messageType, handler)` - Register message type handlers during agent initialization\n   215→- `routeMessage(rawMessage, ws)` - Parse JSON and route to appropriate handler\n   216→\n   217→**Code Location:** [modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts:45-94](../modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts#L45-L94)\n   218→\n   219→```typescript\n   220→async routeMessage(rawMessage: string, ws: WebSocket): Promise<void> {\n   221→    const message = JSON.parse(rawMessage);\n   222→\n   223→    // Check for JSON-RPC 2.0 messages\n   224→    if (isJsonRpcMessage(message)) {\n   225→        await this.jsonRpcRouter.routeJsonRpcMessage(message);\n   226→        return;\n   227→    }\n   228→\n   229→    // Route by message.type\n   230→    const handler = this.handlers.get(message.type);\n   231→    if (handler) {\n   232→        await handler(message, ws);\n   233→    }\n   234→}\n   235→```\n   236→\n   237→### 2. WebSocket Chat Request Handler ([websocket-chat-request-handler.ts](../agents/create-agent/src/websocket-chat-request-handler.ts))\n   238→\n   239→**Responsibility:** Preprocesses incoming ChatRequest messages, validates, and manages conversation state.\n   240→\n   241→**Key Features:**\n   242→- **Session initialization wait** - Ensures session is ready before processing\n   243→- **Conversation busy check** - Prevents concurrent requests for same conversation\n   244→- **Query validation** - Ensures query is non-empty\n   245→- **Query annotations storage** - Stores user-attached entities for enterprise search\n   246→\n   247→**Code Location:** [websocket-chat-request-handler.ts:50-139](../agents/create-agent/src/websocket-chat-request-handler.ts#L50-L139)\n   248→\n   249→```typescript\n   250→async preprocess(message: AgentRequestMessage): Promise<PreprocessResult> {\n   251→    // Wait for session init\n   252→    if (!this.sessionInitCompleted) {\n   253→        await this.onSessionInitCompleted();\n   254→        this.sessionInitCompleted = true;\n   255→    }\n   256→\n   257→    const conversationId = context.conversationId || message.sessionId || uuidv4();\n   258→    const requestId = payload.requestId || uuidv4();\n   259→\n   260→    // Check if conversation is already processing\n   261→    if (this.activeConversations.has(conversationId)) {\n   262→        return {\n   263→            success: false,\n   264→            error: 'CONVERSATION_BUSY',\n   265→            errorMessage: 'Conversation is already processing a request',\n   266→            conversationId,\n   267→            requestId\n   268→        };\n   269→    }\n   270→\n   271→    // Mark as active\n   272→    this.activeConversations.add(conversationId);\n   273→\n   274→    // Validate query\n   275→    if (!userQuery || userQuery.trim().length === 0) {\n   276→        return {\n   277→            success: false,\n   278→            error: 'EMPTY_QUERY',\n   279→            errorMessage: 'Query cannot be empty',\n   280→            conversationId,\n   281→            requestId\n   282→        };\n   283→    }\n   284→\n   285→    // Store query annotations for enterprise search\n   286→    if (queryAnnotations) {\n   287→        this.storeQueryAnnotations(queryAnnotations);\n   288→    }\n   289→\n   290→    return {\n   291→        success: true,\n   292→        requestId,\n   293→        conversationId,\n   294→        processedUserQuery: userQuery,\n   295→        queryAnnotations\n   296→    };\n   297→}\n   298→```\n   299→\n   300→### 3. CreateAgent.handleChatRequest ([create-agent.ts](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts))\n   301→\n   302→**Responsibility:** Main orchestration of the request handling flow.\n   303→\n   304→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:191-815](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L191-L815)\n   305→\n   306→#### Phase 1: Preprocessing & Acknowledgment\n   307→\n   308→```typescript\n   309→const preprocessResult = await this.chatRequestPreprocessor.preprocess(message);\n   310→\n   311→// Send ChatResponse acknowledgment\n   312→if (!preprocessResult.success) {\n   313→    const errorResponse: ChatResponseMessage = {\n   314→        type: MessageType.ChatResponse,\n   315→        success: false,\n   316→        error: preprocessResult.error,\n   317→        errorMessage: preprocessResult.errorMessage,\n   318→        requestId: preprocessResult.requestId,\n   319→        conversationId: preprocessResult.conversationId\n   320→    };\n   321→    wsManager.sendMessage(errorResponse);\n   322→    return false;\n   323→}\n   324→\n   325→// Send success acknowledgment\n   326→const successResponse: ChatResponseMessage = {\n   327→    type: MessageType.ChatResponse,\n   328→    success: true,\n   329→    requestId: preprocessResult.requestId,\n   330→    conversationId: preprocessResult.conversationId\n   331→};\n   332→wsManager.sendMessage(successResponse);\n   333→```\n   334→\n   335→#### Phase 2: Parse Grounding Content\n   336→\n   337→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:242-249](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L242-L249)\n   338→\n   339→```typescript\n   340→// Parse grounding content for clarification questions\n   341→const groundingContentParsed = parseGroundingContent(\n   342→    message.payload.context?.groundingContent || ''\n   343→);\n   344→\n   345→// Append grounding content to query if present\n   346→let finalUserQuery = processedUserQuery;\n   347→if (groundingContentParsed) {\n   348→    finalUserQuery = `${processedUserQuery}\\n\\nAdditional Context: ${groundingContentParsed}`;\n   349→}\n   350→```\n   351→\n   352→The [grounding-content-parser](../agents/create-agent/src/utils/grounding-content-parser.ts) extracts clarification questions from message annotations:\n   353→\n   354→```typescript\n   355→export function parseGroundingContent(groundingContent: string): string | null {\n   356→    const parsedContent = JSON.parse(groundingContent);\n   357→\n   358→    if (parsedContent.messageAnnotations) {\n   359→        for (const annotation of parsedContent.messageAnnotations) {\n   360→            if (annotation.messageAnnotationType === 'ClarificationQuestions') {\n   361→                return annotation.messageAnnotationMetadata.clarificationQuestions;\n   362→            }\n   363→        }\n   364→    }\n   365→\n   366→    return null;\n   367→}\n   368→```\n   369→\n   370→#### Phase 3: Initialize Services\n   371→\n   372→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:254-411](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L254-L411)\n   373→\n   374→Services initialized:\n   375→- `FileWatcherService` - Monitors output directory for file changes\n   376→- `FileEventObserver` - Alternative file monitoring (behind feature flag)\n   377→- `ClaudeMessageLoggerService` - Logs Claude messages to disk\n   378→- `WebSocketMessengerService` - Sends messages to client\n   379→- `DebugZipCreatorService` - Creates debug archives\n   380→- `QueryInterruptManager` - Handles query interruption\n   381→- `ChatHistoryService` - Manages conversation history\n   382→\n   383→#### Phase 4: Create Turn & Execute Hooks\n   384→\n   385→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:294-332](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L294-L332)\n   386→\n   387→```typescript\n   388→// Create a new turn for this chat request\n   389→const turnNumber = await this.workspaceManager.createNewTurn();\n   390→\n   391→// Create turn context for hooks\n   392→const turnContext: TurnContext = {\n   393→    workspaceManager: this.workspaceManager,\n   394→    requestContext: message.payload.context\n   395→};\n   396→\n   397→// Execute startTurn hooks (base + agent-specific)\n   398→const baseHooks = this.hookRegistry.getHooks('base', this.context, turnContext);\n   399→const agentHooks = createAgentHooks(this.hookRegistry, agentName, this.context, turnContext);\n   400→\n   401→if (baseHooks.startTurn) {\n   402→    await baseHooks.startTurn(turnContext);\n   403→}\n   404→\n   405→if (agentHooks.startTurn) {\n   406→    await agentHooks.startTurn(turnContext);\n   407→}\n   408→\n   409→// Store grounding source toggles (behind change gate)\n   410→if (this.context.settingsManager?.changeGate('StoreGroundingSourceToggles')) {\n   411→    await this.storeGroundingSourcesMetadata(message.payload.context);\n   412→}\n   413→\n   414→// Store query annotations (behind change gate)\n   415→if (this.context.settingsManager?.changeGate('StoreQueryAnnotations')) {\n   416→    await this.storeQueryAnnotationsMetadata(message.payload.context);\n   417→}\n   418→```\n   419→\n   420→#### Phase 5: Build System Prompt\n   421→\n   422→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:843-898](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L843-L898)\n   423→\n   424→```typescript\n   425→const systemPrompt = await this.buildSystemPrompt(agentName);\n   426→\n   427→// System prompt includes:\n   428→// - Agent capabilities (Word/Excel/PowerPoint specific)\n   429→// - RAI guidelines\n   430→// - Skill documentation paths\n   431→// - Workspace directory paths\n   432→// - Current timestamp in UTC\n   433→// - Excel clarifications (if enabled)\n   434→// - Context reading instructions\n   435→```\n   436→\n   437→#### Phase 6: Execute Claude Query\n   438→\n   439→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:532-548](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L532-L548)\n   440→\n   441→```typescript\n   442→const queryIterator = claude.query({\n   443→    prompt,\n   444→    options: {\n   445→        model: 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929',\n   446→        maxThinkingTokens: 1024,\n   447→        maxTurns: 2000,\n   448→        systemPrompt,\n   449→        allowedTools,\n   450→        disallowedTools,\n   451→        hooks: combinedHooks,\n   452→        env: {\n   453→            WORKSPACE_DIR: workspaceDir,\n   454→            OUTPUT_DIR: outputDir,\n   455→            SKILLS_DIR: skillDir,\n   456→            SCRIPTS_DIR: scriptsDir,\n   457→            AGENTS_DIR: agentBaseDir,\n   458→            // ... other environment variables\n   459→        },\n   460→        cwd: agentBaseDir\n   461→    }\n   462→});\n   463→```\n   464→\n   465→#### Phase 7: Process Claude Messages\n   466→\n   467→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:554-643](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L554-L643)\n   468→\n   469→\n   470→#### Phase 8: Send Document Notifications\n   471→\n   472→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:648-723](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L648-L723)\n   473→\n   474→```typescript\n   475→// Find generated files\n   476→const generatedFiles = [];\n   477→const outputDirFiles = await readdir(outputDir);\n   478→for (const file of outputDirFiles) {\n   479→    if (file === 'resultMessage.txt' || file.match(/context.*.txt$/)) continue;\n   480→\n   481→    const filePath = join(outputDir, file);\n   482→    const stats = await stat(filePath);\n   483→    if (stats.isFile() && !file.startsWith('.')) {\n   484→        generatedFiles.push({\n   485→            filename: file,\n   486→            filePath: filePath,\n   487→            size: stats.size,\n   488→        });\n   489→    }\n   490→}\n   491→\n   492→// Handle external documents (Excel)\n   493→if (this.externalDocTracker.wasCompleted()) {\n   494→    this.externalDocTracker.sendCompletedNotification(wsMessenger, this.context);\n   495→}\n   496→\n   497→// Find primary document\n   498→const documentFile = generatedFiles.find((f) =>\n   499→    ['.docx', '.xlsx', '.pptx', '.pdf'].some((ext) => f.filename.endsWith(ext))\n   500→);\n   501→\n   502→const selectedFile = documentFile || generatedFiles[0];\n   503→\n   504→if (selectedFile) {\n   505→    const fileExtension = selectedFile.filename.split('.').pop()?.toLowerCase();\n   506→    const isOfficeDocument = ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx'].includes(fileExtension);\n   507→\n   508→    if (this.jsonRpcEnabled && isOfficeDocument) {\n   509→        // Send via JSON-RPC\n   510→        sendArtifactGenerationNotification(requestId, {\n   511→            filename: selectedFile.filename,\n   512→            path: selectedFile.filePath,\n   513→            type: fileExtension\n   514→        });\n   515→    } else {\n   516→        // Send legacy notification\n   517→        await wsMessenger.sendDocumentGenerated(selectedFile.filePath, selectedFile.size);\n   518→    }\n   519→}\n   520→```\n   521→\n   522→#### Phase 9: Cleanup\n   523→\n   524→**Code Location:** [create-agent.ts:739-814](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts#L739-L814)\n   525→\n   526→```typescript\n   527→finally {\n   528→    // Stop services\n   529→    if (fileWatcher) await fileWatcher.stop();\n   530→    if (fileEventObserver) await fileEventObserver.stop();\n   531→    if (chainOfThoughtInitialized) await closeChainOfThought();\n   532→    if (claudeLogger) await claudeLogger.close();\n   533→    if (perfTrackingInitialized) await flushPerfLog();\n   534→\n   535→    // Ensure fallback chat message is sent\n   536→    if (!chatMessageSent && wsMessenger) {\n   537→        let chatMessageContent = 'Something went wrong. Please try again in a moment or start a new chat.';\n   538→        await wsMessenger.sendFileCreatedContent(chatMessageContent, chatMessageResultPath, fileManagerBasePath);\n   539→    }\n   540→\n   541→    // Create debug zip\n   542→    if (debugZipCreator && this.workspaceManager) {\n   543→        await debugZipCreator.create([turnDir], undefined, outputDir, 'generation');\n   544→    }\n   545→\n   546→    // Send task completion notification\n   547→    if (this.jsonRpcEnabled) {\n   548→        sendTaskCompletionNotification(requestId);\n   549→    } else {\n   550→        await wsMessenger.sendFileCreatedContent(resultMessageContent, resultMessagePath, fileManagerBasePath);\n   551→    }\n   552→\n   553→    // Send query interrupted if requested\n   554→    if (this.queryInterruptManager.isInterruptRequested()) {\n   555→        wsMessenger?.sendQueryInterrupted();\n   556→    }\n   557→\n   558→    // Mark conversation as complete\n   559→    if (this.chatRequestPreprocessor && conversationId) {\n   560→        this.chatRequestPreprocessor.markConversationComplete(conversationId);\n   561→    }\n   562→\n   563→    // Fire-and-forget query classification\n   564→    queryClassifier.classifyQuery(message.payload.query);\n   565→}\n   566→```\n   567→\n   568→---\n   569→\n   570→## Key Features\n   571→\n   572→### 1. Conversation State Management\n   573→\n   574→The `WebSocketChatRequestHandler` tracks active conversations to prevent concurrent processing:\n   575→\n   576→```typescript\n   577→private activeConversations = new Set<string>();\n   578→\n   579→// On request start\n   580→this.activeConversations.add(conversationId);\n   581→\n   582→// On request complete (in finally block)\n   583→this.chatRequestPreprocessor.markConversationComplete(conversationId);\n   584→```\n   585→\n   586→### 2. Session Initialization Synchronization\n   587→\n   588→Ensures session initialization completes before processing requests:\n   589→\n   590→```typescript\n   591→if (!this.sessionInitCompleted) {\n   592→    await this.onSessionInitCompleted();\n   593→    this.sessionInitCompleted = true;\n   594→}\n   595→```\n   596→\n   597→### 3. Query Annotations for Enterprise Search\n   598→\n   599→User-attached entities (files, emails, meetings) are stored for enterprise search integration:\n   600→\n   601→```typescript\n   602→private storeQueryAnnotations(queryAnnotations: IQueryAnnotation[]): void {\n   603→    // Store annotations for enterprise search handler\n   604→    this.settingsManager.setFlight('OfficeAgent.EnableSydneyMessageAnnotations', queryAnnotations);\n   605→}\n   606→```\n   607→\n   608→**Query Annotation Structure:**\n   609→```typescript\n   610→interface IQueryAnnotation {\n   611→    id: string;                      // Entity ID\n   612→    QueryAnnotationType: string;     // \"File\", \"Email\", \"Meeting\", \"Chat\", \"Transcript\", \"People\"\n   613→    text: string;                    // Display name\n   614→}\n   615→```\n   616→\n   617→### 4. Grounding Content Parsing\n   618→\n   619→Extracts clarification questions from structured message annotations:\n   620→\n   621→```typescript\n   622→interface MessageAnnotation {\n   623→    messageAnnotationType: 'ClarificationQuestions';\n   624→    messageAnnotationSource: string;\n   625→    messageAnnotationMetadata: {\n   626→        clarificationQuestions: string;\n   627→    };\n   628→}\n   629→```\n   630→\n   631→### 5. Dual Protocol Support (Legacy vs JSON-RPC)\n   632→\n   633→Supports both legacy WebSocket protocol and modern JSON-RPC 2.0:\n   634→\n   635→**Legacy Protocol:**\n   636→```typescript\n   637→await wsMessenger.sendFileCreatedContent(resultMessage, filePath, basePath);\n   638→await wsMessenger.sendDocumentGenerated(filePath, size);\n   639→```\n   640→\n   641→**JSON-RPC Protocol:**\n   642→```typescript\n   643→sendOfficeAgentChatMessage(requestId, resultMessage);\n   644→sendArtifactGenerationNotification(requestId, { filename, path, type });\n   645→sendTaskCompletionNotification(requestId);\n   646→```\n   647→\n   648→### 6. Hook System\n   649→\n   650→Extensible hook system for agent-specific logic:\n   651→\n   652→```typescript\n   653→// Base hooks (shared by all agents)\n   654→const baseHooks = this.hookRegistry.getHooks('base', context, turnContext);\n   655→\n   656→// Agent-specific hooks (WordAgent, ExcelAgent, PowerPointAgent)\n   657→const agentHooks = createAgentHooks(this.hookRegistry, agentName, context, turnContext);\n   658→\n   659→// Merge hooks\n   660→const combinedHooks = mergeHooks(baseHooks.claude, agentHooks.claude);\n   661→\n   662→// Execute startTurn lifecycle\n   663→await baseHooks.startTurn(turnContext);\n   664→await agentHooks.startTurn(turnContext);\n   665→```\n   666→\n   667→### 7. Interrupt Support\n   668→\n   669→Allows users to interrupt long-running queries:\n   670→\n   671→```typescript\n   672→// Check for interrupt in message processing loop\n   673→if (this.queryInterruptManager.isInterruptRequested()) {\n   674→    await queryIterator.interrupt();\n   675→    wsMessenger.sendQueryInterrupted();\n   676→    return true;\n   677→}\n   678→```\n   679→\n   680→### 8. Chat History Handoff\n   681→\n   682→Supports conversation continuity by loading previous chat history:\n   683→\n   684→```typescript\n   685→if (turnNumber === 1 && !this.isNewConversation) {\n   686→    messages = await this.chatHistoryService.fetchChatHistory(sessionId);\n   687→\n   688→    if (messages.length > 0) {\n   689→        chatHistoryHandoff = this.buildHandoffContext(messages);\n   690→\n   691→        // Prefill handoff context\n   692→        for await (const m of claude.query({\n   693→            prompt: `${chatHistoryHandoff}\\n\\nReply exactly: HANDOFF LOADED`,\n   694→            options: { ...options, maxTurns: 1 }\n   695→        })) {\n   696→            if (m.session_id) {\n   697→                prefillSessionId = m.session_id;\n   698→            }\n   699→        }\n   700→    }\n   701→}\n   702→\n   703→// Resume from prefilled session\n   704→const runOptions = prefillSessionId\n   705→    ? { ...options, resume: prefillSessionId }\n   706→    : options;\n   707→```\n   708→\n   709→---\n   710→\n   711→## Error Handling\n   712→\n   713→### Preprocessing Errors\n   714→\n   715→Returned in `ChatResponseMessage`:\n   716→\n   717→| Error Code | Description | Trigger |\n   718→|------------|-------------|---------|\n   719→| `SESSION_INIT_FAILED` | Session initialization failed | Session setup exception |\n   720→| `CONVERSATION_BUSY` | Conversation already processing | Duplicate concurrent request |\n   721→| `EMPTY_QUERY` | Query is empty | Query validation failure |\n   722→| `INTERNAL_ERROR` | Unexpected error | Unhandled exception |\n   723→\n   724→**Example Error Response:**\n   725→```typescript\n   726→{\n   727→    type: MessageType.ChatResponse,\n   728→    success: false,\n   729→    error: 'CONVERSATION_BUSY',\n   730→    errorMessage: 'Conversation is already processing a request. Please wait for the current request to complete.',\n   731→    conversationId: '12345',\n   732→    requestId: '67890'\n   733→}\n   734→```\n   735→\n   736→### Execution Errors\n   737→\n   738→Handled in try-catch and finally blocks:\n   739→\n   740→```typescript\n   741→try {\n   742→    // Main execution flow\n   743→} catch (error) {\n   744→    // Send error notification\n   745→    if (wsMessenger) {\n   746→        wsMessenger.sendDocumentGenerationFailed();\n   747→    }\n   748→    throw error;\n   749→} finally {\n   750→    // Always ensure cleanup and fallback response\n   751→    if (!chatMessageSent && wsMessenger) {\n   752→        await wsMessenger.sendFileCreatedContent(\n   753→            'Something went wrong. Please try again in a moment or start a new chat.',\n   754→            chatMessageResultPath,\n   755→            fileManagerBasePath\n   756→        );\n   757→    }\n   758→}\n   759→```\n   760→\n   761→### Result Message Types\n   762→\n   763→Claude can return different result subtypes:\n   764→\n   765→| Subtype | Description | Action |\n   766→|---------|-------------|--------|\n   767→| `success` | Successful completion | Summarize and send result |\n   768→| `error_max_turns` | Hit max turns limit | Send error message |\n   769→| `error_during_execution` | Execution error | Send error message |\n   770→\n   771→---\n   772→\n   773→## Configuration Flags\n   774→\n   775→The flow is controlled by various feature flags:\n   776→\n   777→| Flag | Purpose | Location |\n   778→|------|---------|----------|\n   779→| `ENABLE_JSON_RPC_FLIGHT` | Enable JSON-RPC protocol | `constants.ts` |\n   780→| `StoreGroundingSourceToggles` | Store grounding sources to file | Change gate |\n   781→| `StoreQueryAnnotations` | Store query annotations to file | Change gate |\n   782→| `DisableMessageAnnotations` | Disable annotation processing | Change gate |\n   783→| `OfficeAgent.EnableExcelClarifications` | Enable Excel clarification questions | Flight |\n   784→| `OfficeAgent.EnableBaseHooksProvider` | Use new hook system | Change gate |\n   785→| `CloseChainOfThought` | Send pending CoT before result | Change gate |\n   786→| `FetchFileContentFromWSMessage` | Include file content in messages | Change gate |\n   787→| `IncludeAllTurnsInDebugZip` | Include all turns in debug archive | Change gate |\n   788→| `SendQueryInterruptedLast` | Send interrupt notification last | Change gate |\n   789→\n   790→---\n   791→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01D1btGNgUTxKhKd2oyCp7xP","session_id":"8a2fc4e6-c1a3-49e6-ae99-e4ee481c1eee","uuid":"32d01c68-32e2-470c-b1b9-90e13b8d80a0"}
