{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D1btGNgUTxKhKd2oyCp7xP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a summary of my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive OfficeAgent Codebase Exploration Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the OfficeAgent codebase, here is a detailed analysis of the architecture and communication patterns:\n\n---\n\n### 1. CLAUDE.md (OfficeAgent Root)\n**File:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/CLAUDE.md` (lines 1-90)\n\nThis is the primary developer guide for the monorepo. Key points:\n- Monorepo structure with agents, modules, devtools, and eval framework\n- **CRITICAL**: Must use PowerShell for yarn/oagent/gulp commands\n- Agent architecture pattern: `registry.ts` (config), agent implementation, prompts with skills/sub-agents\n- Modules organized under `@officeagent/` scope with workspace linking\n- Build system uses Lage task runner with Yarn 4.10.3\n\n---\n\n### 2. Directory Structure\n\n**Agents** (11 total):\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent` - Main document creation agent (DOCX/PPTX/XLSX, Claude SDK)\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/gpt-create-agent` - Azure OpenAI variant\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent`, `ppt-agent`, `ppt-edit-agent` - PowerPoint specialists\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/excel-agent`, `excel-js-runner-agent` - Excel specialists\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/dw-*` - DataWorks agents (accountant, marketer, paralegal)\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/odsp-agent`, `grounding-agent`, `workspace-agent`\n\n**Core Modules** (17 total):\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api` - HTTP/WebSocket API server with routes and handlers\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator` - Provider-agnostic orchestration layer (Claude SDK / Copilot SDK)\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/chain-of-thought` - CoT progress streaming and tracking\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core` - Base agent class, WebSocket manager, settings\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol` - Shared message types and JSON-RPC definitions\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding` - Enterprise search, web search, image search integration\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/excel-headless` - Headless Excel cloud API\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/pptx-assets`, `html2pptx`, `json-to-docx-ooxml` - Format-specific tools\n- Additional: `rai` (Responsible AI filtering), `mcp-proxy`, `git-remote-spo`, `excel-parser`, `verify-slide-html`\n\n---\n\n### 3. HTTP Server & API Routes\n\n**Main Server Setup:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/app.ts` (lines 1-523)\n\nKey Points:\n- **Express HTTP Server** on port 6010 (external), port 6011 (internal)\n- **WebSocket Server** at `/ws` endpoint with 100MB max payload\n- Two separate servers: `externalServer` (public API) and `internalServer` (internal handlers)\n- Environment configuration loaded from `.env` with multiple fallback paths\n- Health check, ping, download, logs, and upload endpoints\n\n**External Routes:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/routes-external.ts` (lines 1-100+)\n- `GET /ping` - Keep-alive endpoint\n- `GET /test` - Extended health check with Playwright browser testing\n- `GET /download` - File download with path validation\n- `GET /health` - Resilience monitoring health status\n- `GET /logs` - Returns and clears log entries\n- `POST /generateDocument` - Main document generation endpoint (async option supported)\n- File upload endpoints with configurable size limits\n\n**Main Endpoint:** `/generateDocument` (lines 218-450)\n- Accepts: `userQuery`, `groundingContent`, `conversationId`, `requestId`, `webSearch`, `enterpriseSearch`, `returnAsync`, `queryAnnotations`, `provisionedFileMetadata`, `sessionId`, `turnNumber`, `requestSource`, `gptIdentifiers`, `scenarioType`\n- Conversation busy state management to prevent concurrent requests\n- Flight flag support for feature testing (e.g., `-enableEnterpriseSearchV2`)\n- Calls `createAgent.run()` which orchestrates the Claude workflow\n\n---\n\n### 4. WebSocket Communication System\n\n**WebSocket Manager:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/websocket/websocket-manager.ts` (lines 1-344)\n\nArchitecture:\n- **Singleton pattern** with `WebSocketManager` class managing all connections\n- **Session tracking**: Maps `sessionId` to `WebSocketSession` objects\n- **Message sending** via `wsManager.sendMessage(message)` to current active client\n- **Automatic connection management** with handshake, disconnect, and error handling\n- **Max payload validation** with configurable size limits (default 100MB, gated at 99MB for safety)\n- Uses `WebSocket.Server` from `ws` library attached to HTTP server\n\nKey Methods:\n- `sendMessage(message)` - Sends JSON-serialized messages to active client\n- `isConnected()` - Checks if client is connected\n- `onSessionInitialized(wsSession)` - Registers session after init\n- `onSessionClosed(sessionId)` - Cleanup on disconnect\n- `setActiveSession(sessionId)` - Switch active session for multi-session scenarios\n\n**WebSocket Router:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts` (lines 1-115)\n\nRouting System:\n- **Type-based routing** - Routes incoming messages by `message.type` field\n- **JSON-RPC support** - Delegates JSON-RPC 2.0 messages to `JsonRpcRouter`\n- **Handler registration** - `registerHandler(messageType, handler)` for custom protocols\n- **Error handling** - Logs unhandled message types\n\nCurrent Handlers:\n- Session initialization\n- LLM proxy (Anthropic API forwarding)\n- MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n- Enterprise search\n- Web search/fetch\n- Image search\n- Excel headless operations\n- Query interruption\n- PPT agent sessions\n\n---\n\n### 5. Agent-to-Frontend Communication Flow\n\n**End-to-End Flow Documented:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md` (790 lines - comprehensive)\n\n**10-Phase Pipeline:**\n\n```\n1. Client sends AgentRequestMessage via WebSocket\n2. Router dispatches to CreateAgent.handleChatRequest()\n3. Preprocessing: validate session, conversation state, query\n4. Send ChatResponseMessage acknowledgment (success/error)\n5. Parse grounding content for clarifications\n6. Initialize services (file watcher, messengers, performance tracking)\n7. Create turn context and execute startTurn hooks\n8. Build system prompt with capabilities, RAI guidelines, skills\n9. Execute Claude query with hooks, stream messages\n10. Send document notifications (artifact/chat messages)\n11. Cleanup: close services, send task completion, debug zip\n12. Client receives: ChatResponse ack, QueryStatus events, DocumentGenerated, TaskCompletion\n```\n\n**Key Message Types:**\n- `ChatResponse` - Acknowledgment with success/error status\n- `QueryStatus` - File created events, generation progress\n- `OfficeAgentTaskUpdateNotification` - Task progress updates (JSON-RPC)\n- `OfficeAgentChatMessage` - Chat responses (JSON-RPC)\n- `SydneyProgressMessage` - Progress with HTML slides, CoT, artifacts\n\n---\n\n### 6. Chain-of-Thought (CoT) Hook System\n\n**Chain-of-Thought Module:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/chain-of-thought/src/` \n\nKey Files and Responsibilities:\n\n1. **Manager** (`manager.ts` lines 1-75):\n   - `initChainOfThought(outputDir, logDir, workspaceDir, locale, flights, contentNotifier)` - Initialize CoT tracking\n   - `trackChainOfThought(message)` - Add message to CoT queue\n   - `closeChainOfThought()` - Finalize and flush\n   - `isChainOfThoughtDisplayed()` - Check if CoT should be shown\n\n2. **Types** (`types.ts` lines 1-69):\n   - `ChainOfThoughtMessage` - Provider-agnostic message interface (assistant, result)\n   - `ChainOfThoughtContentBlock` - Text, tool_use, tool_result blocks\n   - `ChainOfThoughtFlights` - Feature gates (useContentHandler, sendOnlyNewUpdates, useEnhancedHeuristics)\n   - `ChainOfThoughtState` - File handles, queue, processing state\n\n3. **Content Handler** (`content-handler.ts` lines 1-47):\n   - Sends CoT content via `ChainOfThoughtContentNotifier`\n   - `write(message)` - Append to CoT file and send to client\n   - Support for `sendOnlyNewUpdates` flight to replace instead of append\n\n4. **Message Processing** (`message-processor.ts`):\n   - Processes and queues CoT messages\n   - Handles tool_use and result blocks\n   - Deduplication and formatting\n\n5. **Formatter** (`formatter.ts`):\n   - Converts assistant/result messages to readable text\n   - Formats tool names and inputs for display\n\n**Orchestrator Adapter** (`modules/orchestrator/src/cot-adapter.ts` lines 1-100+):\n- Converts Copilot SDK/Orchestrator messages to `ChainOfThoughtMessage` format\n- Deduplicates accumulated text (Copilot SDK sends full content on each event)\n- Maps tool names (view→Read, create→Write, bash→Bash, etc.)\n- Handles sub-agent messages via `parent_tool_use_id`\n\n**Integration in CreateAgent** (`agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts` lines 1-100):\n- Initialize: `initChainOfThought(outputDir, logDir, workspaceDir, locale, flights, contentHandler)`\n- Track messages: `trackChainOfThought(message)` during Claude iteration\n- Cleanup: `closeChainOfThought()` in finally block\n- Sub-agent CoT: `createSubAgentCOTHooks(context, orchestrator, contentHandler)`\n\n---\n\n### 7. How Progression Data Flows to UI\n\n**Notification Functions** (`agents/create-agent/src/utils.ts` lines 1-366)\n\n1. **Chain of Thought Notification** (lines 275-295):\n   ```typescript\n   sendChainOfThoughtNotification(requestId, content)\n   // Sends: SydneyProgressMessage with addToChainOfThought=true\n   // Via: wsManager.sendMessage(OfficeAgentTaskUpdateNotification)\n   // Type: TaskUpdateType.ChainOfThought\n   ```\n\n2. **HTML Slide Progress Notification** (lines 239-268):\n   ```typescript\n   sendHtmlSlideProgressNotification(requestId, slideInfo)\n   // Sends: SydneyProgressMessage with contentGenerationProgressList[].slides\n   // Via: wsManager.sendMessage(OfficeAgentTaskUpdateNotification)\n   // Type: TaskUpdateType.HtmlSlideProgress\n   ```\n\n3. **Artifact Generation Notification** (lines 63-93):\n   ```typescript\n   sendArtifactGenerationNotification(requestId, { filename, path, type })\n   // Sends: SydneyProgressMessage with contentGenerationProgressList[].artifacts\n   // Via: wsManager.sendMessage(OfficeAgentTaskUpdateNotification)\n   // Type: TaskUpdateType.ArtifactGenerated\n   ```\n\n4. **Task Completion Notification** (lines 33-56):\n   ```typescript\n   sendTaskCompletionNotification(requestId, message)\n   // Sends: SydneyProgressMessage with text\n   // Via: wsManager.sendMessage(OfficeAgentTaskUpdateNotification)\n   // Type: TaskUpdateType.StateUpdate, state=Completed\n   ```\n\n5. **Chat Message** (lines 100-118):\n   ```typescript\n   sendOfficeAgentChatMessage(requestId, messageText)\n   // Sends: SydneyMessage with messageType=Chat\n   // Via: wsManager.sendMessage(OfficeAgentChatMessage)\n   ```\n\n**WebSocketMessengerService** (`agents/create-agent/src/services/websocket-messenger-service.ts` lines 1-100+):\n- Integrates with `ChainOfThoughtContentNotifier`\n- `sendFileCreatedContent()` detects file types:\n  - `chainOfThought.txt` → `sendChainOfThoughtNotification()`\n  - `.html` files → `sendHtmlSlideProgressNotification()`\n  - Other files → Legacy file created events\n\n---\n\n### 8. Hook System Architecture\n\n**Hook Registry** (`modules/core/src/`):\n- `HookRegistry` manages per-agent hooks\n- Base hooks: `BaseHooksProvider` (performance, CoT, error tracking)\n- Agent-specific hooks: `WordHooksProvider`, `ExcelHooksProvider`, `PowerPointHooksProvider`\n\n**Hook Providers** (`agents/create-agent/src/hooks/`):\n- `base-hooks.ts` - Shared lifecycle hooks (startTurn, endTurn)\n- `word-hooks.ts` - DOCX-specific validation\n- `excel-hooks.ts` - XLSX-specific operations (blocks direct file writes)\n- `ppt-hooks.ts` - PPTX-specific slide handling\n\n**Claude Hook Adapter** (`modules/orchestrator/src/hooks/claude-hook-adapter.ts` lines 1-150+):\n- Translates generic hooks to Claude SDK format\n- Adapters: `toClaudeHooks()`, `mergeWithClaudeHooks()`\n- Maps `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `SessionEnd`\n\n**Hook Lifecycle in CreateAgent**:\n```typescript\n// Line 75-83: Register hooks in constructor\nthis.hookRegistry = new HookRegistry();\nthis.hookRegistry.register('base', new BaseHooksProvider());\nthis.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.WordAgent, new WordHooksProvider());\nthis.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.ExcelAgent, new ExcelHooksProvider());\nthis.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.PowerPointAgent, new PowerPointHooksProvider());\n\n// Line 398-407: Execute startTurn hooks\nconst baseHooks = this.hookRegistry.getHooks('base', this.context, turnContext);\nconst agentHooks = createAgentHooks(this.hookRegistry, agentName, this.context, turnContext);\nif (baseHooks.startTurn) await baseHooks.startTurn(turnContext);\nif (agentHooks.startTurn) await agentHooks.startTurn(turnContext);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. AugLoop Integration\n\n**Test Client AugLoop Support** (`/.devtools/test-client/src/augloop-client.ts` lines 1-100+):\n\n- Implements `AugLoopClient` class for testing against AugLoop environments\n- Environment endpoints: Test, Int, Dogfood, MSIT, Prod, UsGov, Gallatin\n- Uses `@augloop/runtime-client` and `@augloop/types-core`\n- Supports WebSocket session initialization with annotations\n- HTTP request wrapper: `sendAugLoopHttpRequest()`\n- WebSocket wrapper: `sendAugLoopWsRequest()` with annotation callbacks\n- Token server integration for multi-user/MSA testing\n\n**No direct AugLoop feature within OfficeAgent itself** - AugLoop acts as the orchestration layer that calls OfficeAgent's HTTP/WebSocket APIs\n\n---\n\n### 10. 1JS Framework References\n\n**Search Result:** No explicit 1JS (one-js) or equivalent framework references found in the codebase. The codebase uses:\n- **TypeScript/JavaScript** - Node.js runtime\n- **Express** - HTTP framework\n- **WebSocket (ws library)** - Real-time messaging\n- **Claude Agent SDK** - AI orchestration\n- **Copilot SDK** - Alternative orchestration (for GPT agents)\n- **Office.js** - Excel/Office integration (in agents)\n\nNo evidence of 1JS being integrated or referenced anywhere in the OfficeAgent codebase.\n\n---\n\n### 11. Key Communication Patterns Summary\n\n**Three Communication Modes:**\n\n1. **HTTP REST** (for async operations):\n   - `POST /generateDocument` - Start generation, return immediately with `returnAsync: true`\n   - `GET /download` - Retrieve generated files\n   - `GET /logs` - Stream debug logs\n\n2. **WebSocket (Legacy Protocol)**:\n   - Type-based message routing\n   - `QueryStatus` messages for progress\n   - File created events\n   - Document generation completion\n\n3. **WebSocket (JSON-RPC 2.0)**:\n   - Request/response with correlation IDs\n   - Structured notifications: `OfficeAgentTaskUpdateNotification`\n   - Bidirectional streaming for HTML slides and CoT\n   - Gated by `ENABLE_JSON_RPC_FLIGHT` constant\n\n---\n\n### 12. No \"Cowork\" or Collaboration Features Found\n\nSearch for \"cowork\", \"bebop\", \"collaboration\" (as feature names) found only:\n- General references in example content (\"team collaboration in office\")\n- Domain-specific guidance documents\n- Test case validation keywords\n\n**No dedicated co-authoring, collaboration workspace, or multi-user synchronization features detected** in the core OfficeAgent codebase.\n\n---\n\n### 13. Orchestrator Package Structure\n\n**Files:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator/src/`\n\nKey Components:\n- `factory.ts` - Factory for creating orchestrator instances\n- `harness-builder.ts` - Builds harness configuration\n- `env-builder.ts` - Environment variable setup\n- `types.ts` - Provider-agnostic types\n- `constants.ts` - Configuration constants\n\n**Providers:**\n- `providers/base-orchestrator.ts` - Abstract base\n- `providers/claude-orchestrator.ts` - Claude Agent SDK implementation\n- `providers/ghcp-orchestrator.ts` - Copilot SDK implementation\n\n**Hook System:**\n- `hooks/claude-hook-adapter.ts` - Maps generic to Claude SDK hooks\n- `hooks/types.ts` - Hook interface definitions\n- `cot-adapter.ts` - Converts messages to CoT format\n\n---\n\n## File Path Reference Summary\n\n### Critical Entry Points:\n- **Main Server**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/app.ts`\n- **Router Setup**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts` (lines 27-115)\n- **WebSocket Manager**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/websocket/websocket-manager.ts` (lines 31-233)\n- **Agent Main Class**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts` (lines 50-84)\n- **CoT Tracker**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/chain-of-thought/src/manager.ts`\n- **Notification Functions**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/utils.ts` (lines 33-295)\n- **Messenger Service**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/services/websocket-messenger-service.ts`\n\n### Documentation:\n- **WebSocket Flow**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md`\n- **WebSocket Architecture**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/websocket/README.md`\n- **Create Agent Guide**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md`\n- **Root Guide**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/CLAUDE.md`\n- **Main README**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/README.md`\n\n---\n\nThis completes a thorough exploration of the OfficeAgent codebase with specific focus on agent-frontend communication, CoT streaming, hook systems, and orchestration patterns."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aeb07f4ecc8021f1b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 108507\ntool_uses: 46\nduration_ms: 7